description:
Re-apply the multi-clause body cont-fn fix that fz-duq.4.5 attempted
and reverted. Depends on fz-qbg.1 (SCC fix in typer).

## Change

### `src/ir_lower.rs:921` lower_multi_clause

Replaces the per-clause inline body-then-Return shape with per-clause
body cont fns, mirroring fz-duq.2/.3/.4:

```rust
// After pattern bind + guard test, mint a cont fn capturing the
// post-pattern env; set try_block's terminator to TailCall it.
let cont = mint_cont_fn(ctx, format!("fn_clause_{}", i), clause.span);
let captures = ctx.captured_snapshot();
let capture_vars: Vec<Var> = captures.iter().map(|(_, v)| *v).collect();
ctx.set_term(Term::TailCall {
    callee: cont.id,
    args: capture_vars,
    is_back_edge: false,
});
clause_conts.push(cont);

// After all try_blocks are populated, lower each clause body in its cont fn.
for (i, clause) in fn_def.clauses.iter().enumerate() {
    let _ = switch_to_cont_fn(ctx, &clause_conts[i], 0);
    let result = lower_expr(ctx, &clause.body, true)?;
    if !ctx.terminated {
        ctx.set_term(Term::Return(result));
        ctx.terminated = true;
    }
}
```

### `src/ir_lower.rs` lower_program_full — prelude/user lowering order

The reverted commit also exposed prelude FnId pollution: prelude
multi-clause fns (`print`, `vec_get`, `self`, `send`) mint cont fns
during body lowering. With the current second-pass loop iterating all
fns interleaved, the prelude cont fns get FnIds >= prelude_fn_id_cutoff
and pollute user var_meta in `build_source_info`.

Fix: lower prelude bodies BEFORE registering user fn FnIds, then
bump prelude_fn_id_cutoff to encompass the prelude cont fns:

```rust
// (After prelude registration; before user registration.)
ctx.prelude_fn_id_cutoff = ctx.mb.next_fn_id();
for item in all_items.iter().take(runtime_item_count) {
    if let Item::Fn(fn_def) = item.as_ref() && fn_def.extern_abi.is_none() {
        lower_fn(&mut ctx, fn_def)?;
    }
}
ctx.prelude_fn_id_cutoff = ctx.mb.next_fn_id();

// Then register user FnIds, then lower user bodies.
for item in all_items.iter().skip(runtime_item_count) { ... }
for item in all_items.iter().skip(runtime_item_count) { ... lower_fn ... }
```

This sequencing means ALL prelude FnIds (including their cont fns)
are below the cutoff, and ALL user FnIds (including their cont fns)
are above it. `build_source_info` correctly excludes prelude
var_meta from the user var-name table.

## What's removed

- The 8-line "KNOWN LIMITATION (fz-duq.4.5 follow-up)" comment block
  in `lower_multi_clause` documenting the deferred bug.
- The per-clause `lower_expr(ctx, &clause.body, true)? + if
  !ctx.terminated { set_term(Return) }` stanza at `:966-969`.
- The implicit precondition "no multi-clause clause body may contain
  a non-tail call" — nowhere written down but ruled out half of
  plausible fz programs.

## Tests

- Minimal repro from fz-g8v:
  ```
  fn relay(0), do: receive()
  fn relay(n), do: n
  fn main(), do: print(relay(0))
  ```
  Must not panic. Hangs at receive (no message sent), so test via
  IR-shape inspection rather than running. Or send a message from
  main first.
- All currently-failing-without-this-fix tests must now pass:
  `ir_codegen::tests::count_100k_stays_bounded_via_tail_call_frame_reuse`,
  `ir_codegen::tests::mutual_recursion_even_odd_small_n`,
  `ir_lower::tests::self_recursive_fn_has_back_edge`,
  `ir_lower::tests::pattern_var_records_source_name_and_span`,
  `ir_lower::tests::temp_var_records_span_and_empty_name`,
  `runtime::tests::quiet_quanta_*`, `runtime::tests::mid_flight_gc_*`,
  `runtime::tests::two_processes_survive_mid_flight_gc`.

## Acceptance

- `cargo test --workspace` green.
- `cargo test --workspace golden_clif` zero drift on the four
  multi-clause fixtures (`multi_clause`, `mutual_recursion`,
  `fib_tailrec`, `tail_recursion`). If drift appears: STOP and
  investigate the inliner (don't bless).
- `cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings` clean.
